{
  "id": "RAW_acd33d",
  "title": "OpenAI 与 LangGraph 之争：Agent 构建方法探讨",
  "url": "https://www.latent.space/p/oai-v-langgraph",
  "date": "2025-04-20 23:23:02",
  "author": "Latent.Space",
  "siteName": "Latent Space",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div dir=\"auto\" class=\"body markup\">\n   <p><em><span>Quick reminder: </span><a href=\"https://sessionize.com/ai-engineer-worlds-fair-2025\" rel>AI Engineer CFPs close soon</a><span>! Take a look at “undervalued tracks” like </span><a href=\"https://x.com/swyx/status/1914066019989262527\" rel>Computer Use, Voice, and Reasoning</a><span>, and apply </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/161621318/announcing-the-ai-engineer-mcpllmstxt\" rel>via our CFP MCP</a><span> (talks OR workshops, we’ll figure it out). </span></em></p>\n   <p><em><span>Relevant to today’s quick post we do have an </span><strong>Agent Reliability</strong><span> track. Also: take </span><a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/57QJSF2\" rel>the 2025 State of AI Engineering Survey</a><span>!</span></em></p>\n   <p><span>The AI attention economy has enabled a hypeboi priesthood who exist in a perpetual state of performative orgasmic nirvana, minds continually blown as every launch Changes Everything, vibing at gigahertz oscillations of “it’s so over” vs “so back”. OpenAI’s “</span><a href=\"https://cdn.openai.com/business-guides-and-resources/a-practical-guide-to-building-agents.pdf\" rel>Practical Guide to Building Agents</a><span>” is the latest such earth shatterer:</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffce66548-8530-40df-a357-e7c8e13f3a77_601x487.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9033541f-7cf6-48fb-f0c9-fcf11081d000/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a358480a-265a-48d9-3d57-637c2244a100/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/098a457b-2fe4-49d5-3a8d-81a793718100/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f7c5cce9-7846-4ccb-637f-e9fd8fe8bd00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/81bd0c38-9c30-45ed-4c67-520379a6fb00/public\" width=\"601\" height=\"487\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/fce66548-8530-40df-a357-e7c8e13f3a77_601x487.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:487,&quot;width&quot;:601,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:120714,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161759114?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffce66548-8530-40df-a357-e7c8e13f3a77_601x487.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f2cd5653-743c-48dd-1ed6-26144dea5a00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f9830336-2f69-496a-fe72-cc521cd3cc00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f2ed5a18-d354-4fe0-55f7-57ea4def3900/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/81bd0c38-9c30-45ed-4c67-520379a6fb00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p><span>This guide, however, has been less</span><a href=\"https://x.com/aiDotEngineer/status/1908230651985485955\" rel> well received than Anthropic’s</a><span> equivalent.</span></p>\n   <p><span>If you watch his </span><a href=\"https://latent.space/p/langchain\" rel>multiple</a><span> </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/shunyu\" rel>appearances</a><span> with us, Harrison Chase is not someone who is quick to “anger”, so calling </span><a href=\"https://x.com/aaditsh/status/1912925307386183693\" rel>this guide</a><span> “</span><a href=\"https://x.com/hwchase17/status/1914016302261506421\" rel>misguided</a><span>” and doing a word by word teardown can seem like fighting words for him</span><span class=\"footnote-hovercard-target\"><a data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOM\" id=\"footnote-anchor-1-161759114\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/oai-v-langgraph#footnote-1-161759114\" target=\"_self\" rel class=\"footnote-anchor\">1</a></span><span>.</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F201f144a-3adc-447b-afc2-4b59ac311362_2390x1314.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/d1d64a2f-52fd-4b33-b4ea-e994cf0d7600/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/16c3e735-ea94-487e-2af2-91de943d5a00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/02b1148f-812b-4a53-312a-ee666a6dfd00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9ef85f72-259e-485f-d68f-e5a3bcf69e00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/13c19740-f6c2-4681-fe26-f7feb447a600/public\" width=\"556\" height=\"305.4945054945055\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/201f144a-3adc-447b-afc2-4b59ac311362_2390x1314.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:800,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:556,&quot;bytes&quot;:888841,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161759114?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F201f144a-3adc-447b-afc2-4b59ac311362_2390x1314.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/226bfa12-f195-4e8a-a71f-cff59e8f2c00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/55e88ac9-4954-4e8b-5077-91be2f59eb00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/d5085979-eff7-467f-13d8-a4327efbc900/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/13c19740-f6c2-4681-fe26-f7feb447a600/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>At the heart of the battle is a core tension we’ve discussed several times on the pod - team “Big Model take the wheel” vs team “nooooo we need to write code” (what used to be called chains, now it seems the term “workflows” has won).</p>\n   <p></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Team Big Workflows \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/161759114/team-big-workflows\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p><span>You should read </span><a href=\"https://blog.langchain.dev/how-to-think-about-agent-frameworks/\" rel>Harrison’s full rebuttal</a><span> for the argument, but minus the LangGraph specific parts, the argument that stood out best to me was that you can </span><strong>replace every LLM call in a workflow with an agent and still have an agentic system:</strong></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9e47efdb-80c3-4904-a2d3-ddc595b83139_853x765.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a0d8c994-21ad-4e6a-e042-32d13b090900/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9f84e6e0-0209-40d9-c4dd-0b1a1377e200/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c8b24141-6dbc-4fc2-855c-93fa680a9a00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4dd29a78-d6ce-404b-de13-f6d7f8831700/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9bfd8cc7-a170-4468-84df-caba6b1bc400/public\" width=\"470\" height=\"421.51230949589683\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/9e47efdb-80c3-4904-a2d3-ddc595b83139_853x765.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:765,&quot;width&quot;:853,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:470,&quot;bytes&quot;:119677,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161759114?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9e47efdb-80c3-4904-a2d3-ddc595b83139_853x765.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9e680a99-89ac-4303-0b51-5f14ad4ee300/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f6356e81-7c01-43e4-526e-b95692c06000/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4d26a21c-8a14-4ac8-2c23-7da95f482700/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9bfd8cc7-a170-4468-84df-caba6b1bc400/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p><span>And the ideal agent framework lets you start from one side of the spectrum and move to the other, </span><a href=\"https://overreacted.io/optimized-for-change/\" rel>optimizing for making code easy to change</a><span>:</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0862fbbb-eebe-433b-b8f2-8b814c1a969f_894x585.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ae298149-edd8-4345-2642-f896dc1de000/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/03d38d63-359a-4408-148f-d31f2fecd900/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c363789d-5b45-4f50-22b1-7824df44d500/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/63540e96-9afe-4966-4b0c-611088310400/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/62802798-f06c-4e06-fa99-876fbfb3dc00/public\" width=\"651\" height=\"425.98993288590606\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0862fbbb-eebe-433b-b8f2-8b814c1a969f_894x585.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:585,&quot;width&quot;:894,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:651,&quot;bytes&quot;:66392,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161759114?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0862fbbb-eebe-433b-b8f2-8b814c1a969f_894x585.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/83e538d6-bb3d-443c-f04e-dda7927d0e00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f7c1de55-0e6a-4866-0384-a3ac56a5b200/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4ce48dad-c510-4e6c-edf8-2a3de5276a00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/62802798-f06c-4e06-fa99-876fbfb3dc00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n     <figcaption class=\"image-caption\">\n      the classic tradeoff line that every framework designer walks\n     </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Team Big Model \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/161759114/team-big-model\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p><span>To be clear it’s easy to understand where the Big Model folks are coming from: if you work with Big Lab enough, you’ve seen hundreds of engineer-hours of hand tuned workflows obliterated overnight with the next big model update —&nbsp;the AI Engineer equivalent of learning the Bitter Lesson again and again. This is why “</span><a href=\"https://x.com/swyx/status/1902454997427904865\" rel>AI engineering with the Bitter Lesson in mind</a><span>” was such a resonant topic at the Summit (now at 124k views across platforms):</span></p>\n   <div id=\"youtube2--rsTkYgnNzM\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;-rsTkYgnNzM&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:null,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}\" data-component-name=\"Youtube2ToDOM\" class=\"youtube-wrap\">\n    <div class=\"youtube-inner\">\n     <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/-rsTkYgnNzM?rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0\" frameborder=\"0\" loading=\"lazy\" gesture=\"media\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowautoplay=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\"></iframe>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <p><span>Specifically, I think the success of both OpenAI and </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/gdr\" rel>Gemini’s Deep Research</a><span> this year primarily leveraging O3 to reason through research planning and execution, and later </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/bolt?utm_source=publication-search\" rel>Bolt</a><span> and </span><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xtw6Og7fNG0\" rel>Manus AI</a><span> doing the same with Claude, with very little workflow engineering, has demonstrated that there’s a lot to be said for building general purpose agents that simply augment models without the “inductive bias” constraints of workflows. O-team researcher Hyung Won Chung noted that adding more structure gets you wins in the short term, but that structure tends to lose in performance as the model (pretrain or inference compute) keeps scaling up. </span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F518933ca-2674-4984-9afd-20df1ba73bf6_1188x810.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ec237d1f-5ddf-4412-3f95-fc97bdf4ba00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0212cdd5-aa03-42b4-adbf-c472d1e53200/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0094eb5f-0166-4329-9b1e-d368a9b4da00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7a0307fd-8f84-4065-42be-76457d754800/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/6ede8351-a328-4ec7-c89e-2d40bd508f00/public\" width=\"1188\" height=\"810\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/518933ca-2674-4984-9afd-20df1ba73bf6_1188x810.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:810,&quot;width&quot;:1188,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:194624,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161759114?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F518933ca-2674-4984-9afd-20df1ba73bf6_1188x810.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/514b53d4-65e4-4c1b-0e45-37168d18b200/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0fe05628-9da2-49c5-97a8-49d0704b0f00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/830ed50e-05f5-4cbd-6008-104ee7b69a00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/6ede8351-a328-4ec7-c89e-2d40bd508f00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n     <figcaption class=\"image-caption\">\n      <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kYWUEV_e2ss&amp;t=370s\" rel>from this talk</a><span>. we are using this insight slightly out of context: Hyung Won was making statements about INTERNAL model architecture, but we think it also applies about EXTERNAL systems built around the model — one wonders if he’d also endorse that extrapolation.</span>\n     </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>If your goal is to build AGI, to build a horizontal platform, particularly one targeting non-technical consumers who are confused by even having a model selector, then it’s an understandable position to take, and (even encourage, for the purposes of dataset/human feedback collection).</p>\n   <p></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Workflows AND Agents, not OR \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/161759114/workflows-and-agents-not-or\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>Ultimately the reason I argue Harrison isn’t -actually- taking a fighting stance is he leaves room for the spectrum to exist and makes a remarkably (for someone with obvious skin in the game) balanced argument that you’re going to just want options for doing both:</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F019331c5-299c-4f4e-b103-7cfeb4ae8369_612x488.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f3facb8c-0781-41ee-68d5-4b450f2eef00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/d478ca95-d376-4431-51d2-95cd61c1a800/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c6701076-f570-4318-9fff-8650cd3bf900/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/638913c8-891f-4a98-34b6-aff271fd4100/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f79bf8ea-9f98-4753-9758-80511deb0400/public\" width=\"612\" height=\"488\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/019331c5-299c-4f4e-b103-7cfeb4ae8369_612x488.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:488,&quot;width&quot;:612,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:54021,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161759114?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F019331c5-299c-4f4e-b103-7cfeb4ae8369_612x488.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4778996e-0424-4b3d-6e23-9e8fe0117400/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/98b9ea16-ae30-4545-f75b-78c4c1fa9e00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/bedf8d23-4287-46c2-5926-933ba3d99800/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f79bf8ea-9f98-4753-9758-80511deb0400/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>I find this hard to debate - if meaningful conversation is to be had, it really is more about where the current state of this Pareto frontier really is today (I’m not sure it is convex yet) and how to move it out.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">IMPACT of Agent Frameworks \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/161759114/impact-of-agent-frameworks\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p><span>The other pretty cool thing that Harrison did in his piece was publish </span><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1jzgbANBVi6rNzZVsjZC2CSaCU-byXGlSs0bgy2v2GNQ/edit?usp=sharing\" rel>a full comparison table of all relevant Agent Frameworks today</a><span>, although of course even he couldn’t escape </span><a href=\"https://x.com/swyx/status/1912294047454228736\" rel>the McCormick trap</a><span>. It’s useful to test our </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/agent\" rel>descriptive metaframework of everybody’s Agent definitions</a><span> against a new out-of-distribution Agents definition:</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff0aee6de-16b7-46ed-9040-c4a40accacf9_1640x855.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0d97284e-4b1f-4a93-7c12-b4ba73c1ee00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/40f89baa-c8dd-45ec-c6d6-9a3b1d89ac00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/69ad643d-06b1-4461-823f-19e12b7daf00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/02a90b4f-8b04-47a2-98f1-c43ec093d900/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0cc28111-7715-4bb3-749f-996e0c343800/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"759\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/f0aee6de-16b7-46ed-9040-c4a40accacf9_1640x855.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:759,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:389448,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161759114?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff0aee6de-16b7-46ed-9040-c4a40accacf9_1640x855.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/1a2fa5af-f850-436d-8e08-0fe2a90c8a00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/578b0481-50e3-42a2-d7e3-c3023e17af00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/8e823bb1-7186-4343-960d-d8f83813fb00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0cc28111-7715-4bb3-749f-996e0c343800/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n     <figcaption class=\"image-caption\">\n      IMPACT: Intent, Memory, Planning, Auth, Control flow, Tools. We have subjectively filtered out some frameworks without orchestration, because we view orchestration as very critical for good agent control flow\n     </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p><span>I think this is a remarkably fair shopping list of abstractions and features for the discerning Agent Engineer — it also articulates why you feel certain gaps when an Agent Framework promises you the world and yet you can’t do some things easily.</span><br></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">The Great Debates \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/161759114/the-great-debates\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p><span>If you like this kind of debate, we’re doubling down on the success of </span><a href=\"https://lu.ma/ls\" rel>the Dylan v Frankle showdown</a><span> from last year’s NeurIPS, and also accepting submissions for what we’re calling “The Great Debates” - good faith debaters from two sides of a relevant industry debate. Everybody wins, but the people who are best able to change minds win the most. </span><a href=\"https://sessionize.com/ai-engineer-worlds-fair-2025\" rel>Apply in pairs</a><span>!</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F77b70e86-faa2-4cae-9eaf-cd958863821b_645x566.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/bf6b080f-4739-4d9f-7b48-3113835fbd00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a4b90c9f-55d6-4154-4cc1-1b713b41ca00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/04b8acaa-2949-430b-747e-2284a23b4000/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ddb0b121-2ee7-4559-adaf-674ee9520000/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/51d2e2da-1874-4452-88dc-36e33850d200/public\" width=\"645\" height=\"566\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/77b70e86-faa2-4cae-9eaf-cd958863821b_645x566.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:566,&quot;width&quot;:645,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:111469,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/161759114?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F77b70e86-faa2-4cae-9eaf-cd958863821b_645x566.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null}\" alt srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/3ff4597e-833e-40f9-bbc6-5582ddf64a00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7f452256-cbc0-439f-c2f6-1604f131b700/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/496c1ecf-dac8-4971-b247-151a92cab400/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/51d2e2da-1874-4452-88dc-36e33850d200/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n     <figcaption class=\"image-caption\">\n      <a href=\"https://sessionize.com/ai-engineer-worlds-fair-2025\" rel>https://sessionize.com/ai-engineer-worlds-fair-2025</a>\n     </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p></p>\n   <p></p>\n   <p></p>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOM\" class=\"footnote\">\n    <a id=\"footnote-1-161759114\" href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/oai-v-langgraph#footnote-anchor-1-161759114\" contenteditable=\"false\" target=\"_self\" rel class=\"footnote-number\">1</a>\n    <div class=\"footnote-content\">\n     <p>As I’ll argue: they’re actually not! Harrison is ever the diplomat.</p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "探讨 OpenAI 智能体构建指南与 LangGraph 的差异，围绕大模型驱动与工作流驱动智能体构建方法展开讨论，强调在 Agent 构建策略上融合及权衡的重要性。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "探讨 OpenAI 智能体构建指南与 LangGraph 的差异，围绕大模型驱动与工作流驱动智能体构建方法展开讨论，强调在 Agent 构建策略上融合及权衡的重要性。",
  "summary": "文章深入探讨了 OpenAI 的智能体构建指南与 LangGraph 框架之间的差异和争论，核心在于“大模型接管”与“代码工作流”两种智能体构建策略。OpenAI 倾向于利用大型预训练模型的能力，减少手动编写代码的需求，而 LangGraph 则强调通过精心设计的代码工作流来实现智能体的控制和优化。作者认为，这两种方法并非互斥，而应相互结合，根据实际需求选择合适的方法。同时，文章还介绍了智能体框架的关键能力，如意图理解、记忆、规划等，并对智能体框架进行了比较。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "智能体构建：大模型驱动 vs 工作流驱动",
      "explanation": "OpenAI 提倡利用大模型能力，减少代码干预，LangGraph 则强调代码控制工作流，两种方法各有优劣，适用于不同场景。"
    },
    {
      "point": "理想的智能体框架应能灵活切换大模型与工作流",
      "explanation": "智能体框架应提供从纯大模型驱动到精细工作流控制的平滑过渡，方便开发者根据需求优化智能体行为。"
